  "texts": [
    "Despite the variety of details provided about moderating factors, a common theme emerges that influences the success of PD initiatives.",
    "Among them are the duration of the project, teachers' prior experience, and teachers' geographic location within China (Lin et al. 2024; Lyu et al. 2022).",
    "Notably, regional disparities suggest that access to resources and localized educational policies could significantly affect the outcomes of PD programs.",
    "The findings suggest that while regions such as Zhejiang and Hong Kong are leading in TPD efforts, aligning with national STEM goals, other regions like Hunan and Chengdu require more support to fully contribute to the broader objectives of improving teacher competencies and STEM literacy on a national scale.",
    "Furthermore, there is a growing emphasis on incorporating technology into teaching and improving interdisciplinary communication skills, which reflects the changing demands of STEM education (Huang et al. 2022; Lin et al. 2023)."
  ],
